<p>Several thousand people gathered on Tuesday outside a hotel housing asylum seekers in Saggart on the outskirts of Dublin after reports that a young girl had been assaulted; clashes with police turned violent and six people were arrested, officials said [bbc.co.uk#1][rt.com#1][euronews.com#1][abcnews.go.com#1]. Protesters threw bricks, bottles and fireworks at officers while some set fire to at least one police van, prompting reinforcements and crowd-control measures [firstpost.com#1][straitstimes.com#1][rt.com#1]. Authorities say a suspect has been detained for questioning in connection with the alleged assault; child welfare agency Tusla said the victim was under state care and had absconded from staff during a supervised outing [rt.com#1][bbc.co.uk#1]. The unrest highlights local tensions over accommodation for asylum seekers and has prompted condemnation from senior politicians and calls for a full police inquiry [rt.com#1][euronews.com#1].</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/W1b_MC5arYoMGCKKJ9XlSJWAFT2jsNvFzKlrm1QM8w3JGFa-yaiHxUZ5RgRiiRP12nub6VbBU4bjcZHfrLKxhBG2jqZuS4K2wd6Byhv6YrDP1mRoqNvwOPRdJmKkbkqxhw7F9Zw1draRIv2lyXbU0zvUnu2het3g7qTLC0-BcQ' alt='Protesters clash with police outside a hotel housing asylum seekers near Dublin' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>police response: Gardaí deployed reinforcements and a water cannon to contain the crowd after officers faced &#x27;sustained violence&#x27; from people throwing projectiles [rt.com#1][firstpost.com#1]</li><li>property damage: Protesters burned at least one police van and attacked officers with fireworks, leading to multiple confrontations with law enforcement [straitstimes.com#1][rt.com#1]</li><li>victim background: Tusla, the Child and Family Agency, said the injured girl was in state care and had absconded from staff during a planned recreational trip before the assault was reported [rt.com#1]</li><li>facility context: The hotel targeted by protesters has been converted from the former Citywest Hotel into a permanent migrant shelter, making it a focal point for local anger [rt.com#1][bbc.co.uk#1]</li></ul><blockquote>It is the fundamental duty of the state to protect the children of the state, and irrespective of the complexity or severity of any case, that duty must be fulfilled, - Micheál Martin</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Garda (Irish police): The force said officers were subjected to sustained violence as protesters launched bricks, glass bottles and fireworks at police and six people were arrested. (<a href='https://www.firstpost.com/world/six-arrested-in-dublin-after-protest-outside-migrant-hotel-turn-violent-13943951.html'>Firstpost</a>)</li><li>Tusla (Child and Family Agency): Tusla reported the victim was under state care and had absconded from staff during a planned recreational outing before the assault was reported. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626787-dublin-migrant-hotel-riot/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Irish government (Taoiseach): The prime minister said the state had failed the child and stressed the fundamental duty to protect children in state care. (<a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626787-dublin-migrant-hotel-riot/'>RT</a>)</li><li>Local protesters: People who gathered said they were reacting to the reported assault on a young girl and targeted the hotel housing asylum seekers in anger. (<a href='https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/articles/c629zg8v8jpo'>BBC</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='http://www.euronews.com/2025/10/22/six-arrested-after-anti-immigrant-protest-in-dublin-turns-violent'>Six arrested after anti-immigrant protest in Dublin turns violent</a> - euronews.com</li><li><a href='https://www.straitstimes.com/world/europe/anti-immigrant-protesters-burn-police-van-in-dublin-after-young-girl-attacked'>Anti-immigrant protesters burn police van in Dublin after young girl attacked</a> - straitstimes.com</li><li><a href='https://www.rt.com/news/626787-dublin-migrant-hotel-riot/'>Riot erupts in Dublin after asylum seeke